\c 9
\s1 Ketentuan-ketentuan merayakan Paskah
\p
\v 1 Pada bulan pertama, tahun kedua sejak kami meninggalkan Mesir, berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada saya,
\v 2 “Sampaikanlah kepada umat Israel bahwa mereka boleh kembali merayakan Paskah pada waktunya,
\v 3 yaitu hari keempat belas bulan ini\f + bulan ini- Abib (yang juga disebut Nisan) bulan pertama dalam kalendar Yahudi yang jatuh antara pertengahan bulan Maret sampai dengan pertengahan bulan April.\f*, saat senja/mata hari terbenam. Semua tata cara dan ketentuan harus diikuti. ”
\p
\v 4 Maka saya menyampaikan kepada umat Israel apa yang telah diperintahkan TUHAN mengenai Paskah.
\v 5 Saya menyampaikan kepada umat Israel semua yang sudah difirmankan TUHAN, dan mereka merayakan Paskah di padang gurun Sinai, pada [petang/senja/saat mata hari terbenam], hari keempat belas, bulan pertama yang disebut Nisan.
\p
\v 6 Beberapa orang di perkemhahan Israel sudah menyentuh mayat, dan sebagai akibat menjadi tidak layak untuk beribadah kepada TUHAN, maka mereka tidak dapat merayakan Paskah. Tetapi mereka bertanya kepada Harun dan saya,
\v 7 “Sekalipun kami sudah menyentuh mayat, mengapa kita tidak diperbolehkan untuk merayakan Paskah dan mempersembahkan kurban bakaran kepada TUHAN bersamaan dengan orang lain?!”
\p
\v 8 Saya menjawab, “Sebentar/Tunggu/Sabar, saya akan mendengar/mencari tahu [jawaban TUHAN mengenai hal ini/apa yang TUHAN hendak katakan kepada kalian].”
\p
\v 9 Berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada Musa,/Jadi saya masuk ke daam Kemah Pertemuan dan bertanya kepada TUHAn jawaban apa yang ingin saya sampaikan,]
\v 10 “Sampaikanlah kepada bangsa/umat Israel sebagai berikut, Jikalau kamu atau keturunnmu menjadi najis/tercemar karena keaTell this to the Israeli people: If any of you or your descendants touch a corpse and as a result become unacceptable tome, or if you are away from home on a long trip \add at the time to celebrate thePassover\add*, you will still be permitted to celebrate it.
\v 11 But you must celebrate it exactly one month later, early in the evening of the fourteenth day of that month. Eat the meat of the lamb for the Passover Festival with bread that is baked without yeast and eat bitter herbs.
\v 12 Do not leave any of it until the next morning. And do not break any of the lamb's bones. Obey all the regulations about celebrating the Passover.
\v 13 But if any of you has not done anything that would make you unfit to celebrate the Passover Festival, and you are not away from home on a long trip, and you do not sacrifice to me at the proper time, you will no longer be allowed to associate with my people. ◄You will be punished/I will punish you►.
\p
\v 14 Foreigners who live among you may also celebrate the Passover Festival, if they obey all my commands concerning it.”
\s1 A cloud covered the Sacred Tent
\p
\v 15-16 On the day that the Sacred Tent was set up, a cloud covered it. But from the time that the sun set until the time thatthe sun rose \add the next day\add*, the cloud resembled a \add huge\add* fire. And that is what happened every day\add that we Israelis were in the desert\add*
\v 17 When the cloud rose up and started to move \add to a new location\add*, the Israelis followed it. When the cloud stopped, the Israelis stopped there and set up their tents.
\v 18 We traveled when Yahweh, \add by causing the cloud to move orstop\add*, told them when to move and when to stop. When the cloud stayed over the Sacred Tent, we Israelis stayed at that place.
\v 19 Sometimes the cloud stayed over the tent for a long time, so when that happened, we did not travel.
\v 20 Sometimes the cloud remained over the tent for only a few days. The people stopped and set up their tents as Yahwehcommanded them, and we traveled\add to a new location\add* when Yahweh commanded them to do that.
\v 21 Sometimes the cloud stayed in one place for only one day. When that happened, when the cloud rose up\add into the sky\add* the next morning, then we traveled. Whenever the cloud moved, during the day or during the night, we traveled.
\v 22 If the cloud stayed over the Sacred Tent for two days, or for a month, or for a year, during that time we stayed where we were. But when the cloud rose up into the sky, they started to travel.
\v 23 When Yahweh commanded us to \add stop and\add* set up their tents, they did that. When he told them to move, they moved. We did whatever Yahweh told Moses/me that they should do.